From 82082a493f50ab7955f19ff3f5ffb02e748ae834 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DOSKUTSU NXEngine Port <services.claude@accounts.ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:59:16 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [DOSKUTSU] djgpp: replace spdlog with fmt-backed Logger shim
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: spdlog (vendored in deps/spdlog/) is non-viable on the
DJGPP cross-toolchain for two independent reasons identified by task #34's
investigation:

1. `SPDLOG_WCHAR_FILENAMES` is unconditionally enabled in the vendored
   `deps/spdlog/tweakme.h:59` — not the originally-suspected
   `SPDLOG_WCHAR_TO_UTF8_SUPPORT`. The macro pulls
   `<spdlog/fmt/xchar.h>` which references `std::fputws` and
   `std::wostream`. DJGPP's libstdc++ provides neither — wide-stream
   support is missing. Compilation fails before linking with
   `'fputws' is not a member of 'std'` and `'wostream' is not a member of
   'std'`.

2. `std::mutex` is not instantiable on DJGPP 12.2.0 — `_GLIBCXX_HAS_GTHREADS`
   is undefined because there's no pthread runtime to back it. spdlog's
   `*_mt` sink typedefs (`stdout_color_sink_mt`, `basic_file_sink_mt`)
   instantiate `std::mutex` at static-construction time, and the global
   spdlog registry holds a mutex unconditionally even if you only use
   `*_st` sinks. Switching the sink type does not avoid the registry's
   mutex; the whole library is unusable.

The path forward, ratified in #29 architecture brief revision per #34's
findings: drop spdlog on DJGPP only, replace with a thin fmt-backed
shim that preserves the LOG_TRACE / LOG_DEBUG / LOG_INFO / LOG_WARN /
LOG_ERROR / LOG_CRITICAL macro surface verbatim. NXEngine has ~280 LOG_*
call sites; preserving the macro surface means zero call-site edits.

Files added:
- `src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h` (~120 lines): the shim. Contains:
  * `extern std::FILE *djgpp_log_fp` and `extern int djgpp_log_level`
    (both defined in Logger.cpp's DJGPP branch).
  * Internal `DJGPP_LOG_(level, name, ...)` macro that level-filters
    short-circuit, formats with `fmt::format_to(std::back_inserter(buf),
    ...)`, and writes the resulting `fmt::memory_buffer` to both the log
    FILE* (if open) and stderr.
  * Six `LOG_*(...)` macros aliasing `DJGPP_LOG_` with the right level.
  * Minimal `spdlog::level::level_enum` + `spdlog::set_pattern` /
    `spdlog::set_level` / `spdlog::flush_on` no-op stubs so Logger.cpp's
    DJGPP init path can avoid wrapping every call in `#ifdef`s.

Files modified:
- `src/Utils/Logger.h`: `#ifdef __DJGPP__` gate. DJGPP gets
  `#include "Logger_djgpp.h"` (which defines LOG_* directly); other
  platforms keep `#include <spdlog/spdlog.h>` + the existing
  `#define LOG_TRACE SPDLOG_TRACE` aliases.
- `src/Utils/Logger.cpp`: spdlog sink-setup code preserved on non-DJGPP.
  DJGPP branch declares the shim's `djgpp_log_fp` + `djgpp_log_level`
  storage, then `init()` `fopen()`s the log file in text mode (CRLF
  line endings desired for DOS log readers) and sets the level based
  on `DEBUG`. fopen failure logs to stderr and continues — log noise
  remains visible even when the configured path can't be written.

Behaviour deltas vs. upstream spdlog:
- No async sink, no log rotation, no thread-id tagging. NXEngine doesn't
  use any of these on Linux/Windows either (the existing init() only
  installs basic_file_sink + stdout_color_sink synchronously).
- Log pattern is hardcoded to `[HH:MM:SS] [LEVEL] message`. The
  `set_pattern(LOG_PATTERN)` call from Logger.cpp's non-DJGPP branch
  becomes a no-op on DJGPP. Sub-second precision (`%e` in upstream)
  dropped — `time()`+`localtime()` is enough for human-readable DOS
  logs and avoids pulling in chrono machinery.
- No ANSI colour. DOS stdout is a single stream where escape codes
  would be visible literal noise unless an ANSI driver is loaded.

Verified: standalone DJGPP+SDL3 sanity-compile of a tiny driver exercising
Logger::init + every LOG_* macro succeeds with `-fsyntax-only`. Macro
expansion is tight: a disabled-level call site emits
`if (level >= djgpp_log_level) { ... }` around the formatting, so
LOG_TRACE under -DDEBUG=0 short-circuits to a single integer compare.

This is patch slot 0006-0009 (reserved for future DOS concerns per #29
brief). The DJGPP series now extends from 5 to 6 patches; tech-writer
should reflect the expansion in patches/nxengine-evo/README.md when this
lands. The patch is orthogonal to the SDL3 migration patches (0010-0018)
— neither touches `src/Utils/`.
